CRITICAL TIMING NOTES:
-----------------------

⏱️  "Warm-up" (Phase 1): Must stay ≤6 min. If you take 8 min on Target 1.1, you 
   lose 2 min of surplus. Discipline required. It's the easiest target; treat it as such.

⏱️  "Complexity Peak" (Phase 3): Target 1.3 is the hardest (8 marks). Allocated 
   8 min. If it takes 10 min, you've lost 2 min but still have 49-min surplus. 
   NOT a crisis. But practice this target to lock it in 8 min.

⏱️  "Victory Point" (Minute 32): After Phase 5, you have 32/30 marks. STOP seeking 
   more marks. The goal is not maximum marks; it is PSYCHOLOGICAL DOMINANCE. Shift 
   to verification mode.

⏱️  "Verification Window" (39-70 min): Deploy sentinels SLOWLY. Do not rush. This 
   is where precision beats speed. A 10-second Z-check that catches an error is 
   worth more than finding one new mark.

